http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 5 Oct 2018
Source: OIE, WAHID [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=28180


Bluetongue (BTV), Italy
-----------------------
Information received on 5 Oct 2018 from Dr. Silvio Borrello, Chief Veterinary Officer, Food Safety and Collegial Bodies for Health Protection, Ministry of Health, Department for Veterinary Public Health, Rome, Italy

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 19 Sep 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 3 Oct 2018
Reason for notification: New strain of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus (BTV)
Serotype: 3
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 8
New outbreaks (8)

[According to the immediate notification report, the 8 outbreaks of BTV-3 occurred in the following regions: Puglia/Apulia (1), Sardegna/Sardinia (7). See details of each outbreak at the source URL above. - Mod.CRD]

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 8
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Sheep / 1593 / 96 / - / - / -
Goats / 200 / 4 / - / - / -

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / 6.03 / ** / ** / **
Goats / 2 / ** / ** / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country, screening, zoning, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type:
Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute (IZSAM), Teramo (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Goats / Real-time PCR / 3 Oct 2018 / Positive
Sheep / Real-time PCR / 3 Oct 2018 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

